cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CY 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with the generation of human-like text using generative models. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as these fields are closely related to natural language generation. Additionally, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CY (Computers and Society) could also be possible sub-categories as the paper discusses the impact of sampling strategies and text excerpt length on the performance of automatic detection methods and human raters.
